body:
To @sandhyasun and @selvaganesang: 

I just pushed reworks with the following changes:

1. Changed ExLob to be allocated off the Lob Heap (and making its lobDataFile_ member an NAString instead of a string)
2. Changed the handling of stack variables to avoid global heap allocations
3. Added an error check on the externaltolob function: If the file name is longer than 256 characters (= MAX_LOB_FILE_NAME_LENGTH), then I raise a new error, 8557. By preventing over-long file names from being stored in LOB descriptors, we prevent buffer overruns at the SQL_EXEC_LOBcliInterface level. This is a temporary solution; in the long run the SQL_EXEC_LOBcliInterface call must be enhanced to deal with the case that the proper black box length is not known in advance. (I'll write a separate JIRA on that issue.)

I've pushed these changes so you can review them. Please don't merge just yet, as I'd like to add a check in regression test executor/TEST130 to test for the new error. Also it hasn't been regression tested yet.
@svarnau ,that's a good idea. `trafodion` user should be an application user like `hdfs`, `hbase` and donnot requrie a password.
This looks ready to merge ? And it shoudl address the intermittent TEST130 failure due to resource issue on HDP as well ?
Yes. It is ready for merge. Should address Test130 failure. Thank You.

Second rework includes:

1. Replaced a string stack variable with dynamic char arrays to avoid using global heap. (I intended to fix this one on the previous rework but missed it.)
2. Added a test to executor/TEST130 to test the new 8557 message.
3. Added documentation for the new 8557 message to the Messages Guide.

+1. Changes look good. 
I can merge this in by the end of today if there are no concerns. @selvaganesang has promised to address some issues in a subsequent delivery.

Thanks for the review. 
Fixed all of review feedback. 
1. bufLen checked.
2. Stack trace buffer size define.
3. Regarding ignore of invalid plans, stack trace is also not logged. stack trace logged only in case of error return.
4. Stack trace for executor is captured in SQLMXLoggingArea::logSQLMXAssertionFailureEvent() in path of assert_botch_abend().
@sandhyasun and @selvaganesang: I think I've addressed all the issues brought up. I plan to commit this tomorrow evening if no further issues arise.
@narendragoyal and @sbroeder, you might want to review the process.cxx change.

Changes look good  though I have provided some comments for you to consider.

 Actually this comment should have gone in #929. Added here by mistake
Changes look good though I have provided some comments for you to consider
The change looks benign. But, is there a need to run full regressions with this change?
Full regressions were on my workstation. Thanks.
Looks good .  I iwll merge this is in a short while if there are no further comments.
Oopes before that  shouldn' there be a testcase to cover this ? I didn't see a new testcase added to the sort regression test ?
I think merging it is fine. I agree adding a test case would be good; that could be done as a separate pull request.
The extra test is a success, compGeneral/TEST042 passes, the other tests (and failures) are irrelevant.
+1 looks good to me. Thanks for removing the "get tables" from schema trafodion."_HV_HIVE_", that made the test fail on my workstation pretty much every time.
Thanks for the review. I have added a test case to regression test that covers this case.
